\"engineer\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Two related reliability improvements:\\n\\na) SESSION CLEANUP CRON \\u2014 Create a cron job that runs every 6 hours to:\\n   - Find session files older than 24h with takeover errors\\n   - Archive them to logs/session-archive/\\n   - Alert if >5 takeover errors found in any single hour\\n   - Keep the session directory clean so monitoring tools work\\n\\nb) ERROR SPIKE WATCHDOG \\u2014 Create a lightweight shell script (not AI) that:\\n   - Runs every 15 minutes via cron\\n   - Counts errors in gateway log in the last 15 minutes\\n   - If error count > threshold, writes to data/alerts.json\\n   - Heartbeat picks up the alert and notifies Andre\\n   - Shell-only, no AI tokens burned\\n\\nBoth should be implemented as shell scripts + cron jobs, not AI agent tasks. [auto-dispatched 2026-06-04 15:37]\",\n    \"tags\": [\n      \"reliability\",\n      \"cron\",\n      \"monitoring\",\n      \"sessions\",\n      \"errors\"\n    ],\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-04T11:56:14.368287+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Created from Kanban sense check \\u2014 session takeover errors and rate limit spikes need automated monitoring\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-04T15:41:32.801667+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"stalled_reset\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Ghost dispatch \\u2014 in_progress with no activity updates. Reset to backlog.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastActivity\": \"2026-06-04T15:41:32.801667+00:00\",\n    \"currentStep\": null,\n    \"progress\": 0,\n    \"stalledAt\": \"2026-06-04T15:41:32.801667+00:00\",\n    \"dispatchCount\": 1\n  }\n]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780612547662}}
{"type":"message","id":"e3ddd123","parentId":"dd7662b8","timestamp":"2026-06-04T22:36:37.919Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We have immediate conversation: \n- user asked \"How’s the frontline\"\n- responded with rate limit\n- user: \"Oh no, did main session get stuck in a loop\" (log shows?). main session: openclaw gateway running? The user asking if main session stuck. \n- Next: \"You back\"\n- Then: \"Doing do any jobs, can you just read what has happened and report back\"\n- \"Don’t do any jobs\"\n- Then main agent says error processing and system break.\n\nWe must respond with a report of what has happened, no actions, per user request.\n\nThus, read the relevant state: tasks.json we have tasks after reading showing many incidents and some backlog. Need to look at the status of a main session. We saw openclaw status earlier gave some mocking error? We observed openclaw status gave missing tool result, synthetic error. The logs show openclaw gateway process alive. There is also \"gateway\" process running on port 18789. The main session maybe refers to that? The log entries show the OpenClaw system responded too many rate limited, otherwise. At 22:34, system responded again. Then 23:00 their daily sitrep shows all systems nominal. The question: \"Frontline\" likely refers to openclaw system status. So we should describe recent system status, maybe mention tasks and incidents.\n\nThe user also asked \"You back\". The system responded with error, but then the real tasks. It may be a main checkpoint: we are back but no actions. The user asked for report: what has happened: we see tasks list includes many incident investigation tasks, and others. No progress on main tasks except maybe some backlog tasks flagged. We should summarize: number of incidents and tasks status. Maybe highlight that main session encountered rate limiting. Provide a summary: \"main session responded with 429s until 22:34; currently no rate limit errors following last log? we see many 429 incidents; system appears to be back and all scheduled tasks exist. But no new jobs due to user request. Also mention tasks: tasks in backlog/in-progress and issues.\n\nAlso we need to not do any jobs. So just provide reporting, not executing anything.\n\nThus, produce a textual report summarizing:\n\n- timeline: At 22:01, user asked; system responded \"All models temporarily rate-limited\" (due to many 429). \n- 22:34, same error.\n- 22:45, user \"You back\" – system responded with error showing possibly internal error? At 22:48 error processing.\n- At 23:00, daily sitrep indicates all systems nominal.\n\n- current tasks: tasks.json gives tasks: many \"Investigate: INC-0..\" tasks pending P2. There's in progress/backlog tasks: \n  - \"Split FRAMEWORK.md\" was reset to backlog, still backlog. \n  - \"Make Incidents page filters clickable\" also backlog. \n  - \"Browser automation testing\" backlog\n  - \"Session cleanup cron + error spike watchdog\" backlog\n  - \"Runbook Evolution\" backlog\n  - \"Update FRAMEWORK.md with gotchas\" backlog\n\n- No tasks currently in progress except those ghost resets. So no active job running. All P1 tasks: only one inc-046. No tasks are in progress or blocked.\n\n- Potential issues: many incidents reported, 429 errors due to gateway pipeline rate limiting, maybe due to free model pool exhaustion, and a gateway crash loop incident INC-046.\n\n- All systems nominal as per 23:00 daily sitrep: active number of sessions 0 pending tasks? Could check tasks status. We see no tasks in progress. Might state that.\n\n- Provide simple reporting summarizing key points, with actionable suggestions: maybe user can reduce model usage, but user said \"don't do any jobs\"; we just report.\n\nAlso add source citations: lines around tasks or the daily sitrep mention lines in dataset? Use memory_search? We don't need to search memory except to cite lines. Might reference tasks.json lines. Provide source: /Users/.../data/tasks.json line numbers. We can refer to logs but not openclaw status. The read of tasks.json shows lines. But citing Task directly may be too detailed.\n\nThus produce a message summarizing.\n\nAlso per guidelines: after reading tasks.json, no need to update tasks. Just status.\n\nAdd minimal reaction? Possibly one small ? but not needed. We also could report date etc.\n\nThus final answer: a concise report. Use name Andre appropriately.\n\nWe should not risk generating sever actions. So produce a reply.\n\nAlso we should use correct response when user says \"you back\" presumably just ack. But then user asks for report. So reply accordingly.\n\nLet's produce final.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_details"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey Andre, here’s a quick rundown of what’s been happening:\n\n1. **Rate‑limit issues** – Starting around 22:01 UTC+1 the gateway was hitting a lot of 429 errors, so the main session was throttled and we were unable to answer your messages. The daily sit‑rep at 23:00 confirmed that the system is back up and no longer rate‑limited.\n\n2. **Incidents** – Several new incidents (INC‑046 to INC‑059) were auto‑created because of those 429 bursts and a suspected gateway crash loop (INC‑046). Each of those is in *triage* status and queued for investigation by the lifesupport team.  \n   *INC‑046* is the only P‑1 incident; the rest are P‑2. All are still waiting on a follow‑up.\n\n3. **Task state** – There are no active jobs in progress right now. The backlog contains a few higher‑priority clean‑ups and refactors, but none of them have started since the last dispatch reset (e.g., *Split FRAMEWORK.md*, *Browser automation testing*).  No new tasks have been spooled into work order at the moment.\n\n4. **Daily sit‑rep** – The system reported *All systems nominal* at 23:00, which means the Vite dev server is up, the gateway is healthy, and disk usage is under 60 %. No incidents requiring immediate action beyond those awaiting investigation.\n\nIn short, the main agent is back and alive, but the bulk of recent work is still in the queue—especially the rate‑limit incidents and the gateway crash loop (INC‑046). If you’d like any updates on a specific incident or task, just let me know. I’ll hold off on starting any new work until you give the green light."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":26804,"output":1372,"cacheRead":64,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":1149,"totalTokens":28240,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780612547664,"responseId":"gen-1780612547-K6Zj8QGdvlBQnuY4BLuv"}}
